[![Diwali in Yokohama 2017](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2017/10/snip_20171029205000-800x450.png)](https://youtu.be/nt1fQ3Sm7RQ)

Part of Diwali celebrations in Yokohama, Japan in October 2017. Screencap from
[deharu monkiye YouTube channel](https://youtu.be/nt1fQ3Sm7RQ).

Diwali, often referred to as the “[Hindu festival of
lights](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diwali),” is [one of the most
important](http://www.drikpanchang.com/diwali/diwali-puja-
calendar.html?l=11960) festivals[ observed by the Indian diaspora every
year](http://www.theholidayspot.com/diwali/around_the_world.htm) in some
countries around the world, and Japan is no different.

While in 2017 Diwali begins on October 19, [about 200,000
people](https://tokyocheapo.com/events/diwali-yokohama/), mostly Japanese,
were estimated to have attended an annual two-day Diwali cultural event in the
city of Yokohama [on October 14 and 15](http://diwaliyokohama.org/), making it
one of the largest India-related festivals in Japan. The festival took place
next to Yamashita Park, one of Yokohama's best known parks, on the waterfront
near the city's historic [Chinatown](http://www.japanvisitor.com/japan-city-
guides/yokohama-china-town-chukagai).

> 横浜でインドに浸れる2日間。
